#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.221"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.221:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: sucaritavaggo (bj) | sucaritavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.221:0.2"
msgid "23. Duccaritavagga"
msgstr "23. Bad Conduct"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: vacīsucaritasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.221:0.3"
msgid "221. Duccaritasutta"
msgstr "221. Verbal Conduct"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.221:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīduccaritāni."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech."

msgctxt "an4.221:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.221:1.3"
msgid "Musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo—"
msgstr "Speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical."

msgctxt "an4.221:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīduccaritāni."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech."

msgctxt "an4.221:1.5"
msgid "Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīsucaritāni."
msgstr "There are these four kinds of good conduct by way of speech."

msgctxt "an4.221:1.6"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: saṇhā vācā, mantavācā → saṇhavācā mantābhassaṃ (sī ), saṇhā vācā mantābhāsā (syā1-3, kaṃ), saṇhavācā mantāvācā (pā1)
msgctxt "an4.221:1.7"
msgid "Saccavācā, apisuṇā vācā, saṇhā vācā, mantavācā—"
msgstr "Speech that’s true, harmonious, gentle, and thoughtful."

msgctxt "an4.221:1.8"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīsucaritānī”ti."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of good conduct by way of speech.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.221:1.9"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
